---
import Layout from "../layout/layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
    <div class="article-container">
        <div class="hero-image">
            <img src="/new3-2.jpeg" alt="Image" />
        </div>

        <span class="category"> INDIE NEWS </span>

        <h1 class="article-title">
            GamerFest Dublin: Ireland’s Biggest Gaming Festival Returns
        </h1>

        <div class="article-meta">By Fathima • May 2026 • 5 min read</div>

        <div class="article-intro">
            A newly emerging Irish studio has revealed its first major title,
            bringing together open-world exploration and narrative-focused
            gameplay.
        </div>

        <div class="article-content">
            <p>
                Gaming culture in Ireland continues to grow, and one of the
                country’s most anticipated gaming events is GamerFest Dublin.
                Returning to the RDS in Dublin on 23–24 May 2026, the festival
                brings together gaming, esports, technology, and entertainment
                under one roof. GamerFest has become one of Ireland’s largest
                gaming events, attracting thousands of visitors from across the
                country and beyond.
            </p>

            <p>
                The event offers a wide variety of activities for gaming fans.
                Visitors can experience the latest video games, take part in
                esports competitions, explore virtual reality experiences, and
                meet gaming content creators and special guests. Cosplay events,
                live stages, gaming merchandise, and interactive exhibits are
                also major attractions during the festival.
            </p>

            <p>
                For indie game developers, GamerFest also provides an
                opportunity to showcase their work to a wider audience. Recent
                announcements highlighted a dedicated GameDev Zone, creating
                space for game creators to present projects, connect with
                industry professionals, and engage directly with players.
            </p>

            <p>
                Since launching in 2017, GamerFest has expanded significantly
                and evolved into more than just a gaming convention. It now acts
                as a community event that connects players, developers,
                creators, and industry professionals. As Ireland’s gaming
                industry continues to develop, events like GamerFest play an
                important role in supporting local talent and strengthening the
                country’s gaming culture.
            </p>

            <div class="inline-image">
                <img src="/new3.jpg" alt="Image" />
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</Layout>
